  "text": "This analysis identifies all Java source files in apache/kafka that validate SASL mechanism configuration at broker startup. The validation occurs at multiple levels:\n\n## Broker Startup Initialization Chain:\nDuring broker startup in BrokerServer.scala (line 79-82), a DelegationTokenCache and CredentialProvider are created, which calls ScramCredentialUtils.createCache() to initialize credential caches for all SCRAM mechanisms (SCRAM-SHA-256, SCRAM-SHA-512).\n\n## Configuration Validation:\n1. **BrokerSecurityConfigs.java** (lines 97-99) defines the `SASL_ENABLED_MECHANISMS_CONFIG` constant that lists enabled mechanisms and validates against a default list containing only GSSAPI.\n\n2. **KafkaConfig.scala** (lines 627-629) validates that if inter-broker communication uses SASL, the configured `sasl.mechanism.inter.broker.protocol` must be included in the `sasl.enabled.mechanisms` list.\n\n## JAAS Configuration Validation:\n**JaasContext.java** (lines 65-74) loads server context for each mechanism, performing critical validation:\n- Checks that listenerName and mechanism are not null (lines 66-69)\n- Validates JAAS configuration entries exist (lines 92-96)\n- Ensures exactly one JAAS login module is configured (lines 97-98)\n\n## Channel Builder and Callback Handler Setup:\n**ChannelBuilders.java** (lines 137-140) creates JAAS contexts for all enabled mechanisms in server mode, iterating through each mechanism and calling JaasContext.loadServerContext().\n\n**SaslChannelBuilder.java** (lines 317-336) creates mechanism-specific callback handlers:\n- For PLAIN: PlainServerCallbackHandler (line 327)\n- For SCRAM: ScramServerCallbackHandler with credential cache (line 329)\n- For OAUTHBEARER: OAuthBearerUnsecuredValidatorCallbackHandler (line 331)\n- For custom: Instantiates configured handler class (line 325)\n\n## Server Authenticator Validation:\n**SaslServerAuthenticator.java** (lines 177-189) in its constructor validates:\n- No SASL mechanisms are empty (lines 179-180)\n- Every enabled mechanism has a callback handler (lines 182-184)\n- Every enabled mechanism has a Subject configured (lines 185-186)\n\n## Mechanism-Specific Configuration:\n1. **SCRAM Configuration**: CredentialProvider.java (lines 31-34) calls ScramCredentialUtils.createCache() which validates credential caches are created for all enabled SCRAM mechanisms.\n\n2. **PLAIN Configuration**: PlainServerCallbackHandler.java (lines 42-44) configures JAAS entries and validates authentication during runtime (lines 61-70).\n\n3. **OAUTHBEARER Configuration**: OAuthBearerUnsecuredValidatorCallbackHandler.java (lines 114-123) validates:\n   - SASL mechanism equals OAUTHBEARER (line 115)\n   - Exactly one JAAS configuration entry exists (lines 117-120)\n\n4. **GSSAPI Configuration**: SaslChannelBuilder.java (lines 349-355) detects GSSAPI presence to select appropriate login class (KerberosLogin), with native GSS credentials validation in lines 374-376.\n\nAll these components work together to ensure comprehensive validation of SASL mechanisms at broker startup, from configuration parsing through runtime authentication handler initialization."
}

